hands_on_practices.problem:
Let $(a,b)$ be a pair of integers for which there exist integers $x$ and $y$ satisfying the equation $ax+by=1$. Let $d$ be the greatest common divisor (GCD) of the two integers $2a+3b$ and $3a-2b$. Which one of the following sets represents the complete set of all possible values for $d$?

A. {1}
B. {1, 5}
C. {1, 13}
D. {1, 5, 13}
E. {1, 7, 13}
